- We know there are several scaling models out there.

2
00:00:04.030 --> 00:00:07.030
Let's take a look at the Scaled Agile Framework,

3
00:00:07.030 --> 00:00:11.030
SAFe for short, and why an arm of the US Government,

4
00:00:11.030 --> 00:00:14.000
Fannie Mae has chosen it.

5
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Fannie Mae is the largest provider

6
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.070
of mortgage financing in the US.

7
00:00:18.070 --> 00:00:21.080
After the housing crisis in 2013,

8
00:00:21.080 --> 00:00:25.020
Fannie Mae recognized that it needed to be more responsive

9
00:00:25.020 --> 00:00:27.080
to changing customer demands.

10
00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:31.060
The SAFe model is all about alignment and collaboration

11
00:00:31.060 --> 00:00:35.000
across large numbers of Agile teams.

12
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:38.030
It relies heavily on Agile software development,

13
00:00:38.030 --> 00:00:42.030
Lean product management and systems thinking.

14
00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:44.060
SAFe has Scrum or Kanban teams

15
00:00:44.060 --> 00:00:46.050
at the foundation of the model.

16
00:00:46.050 --> 00:00:49.070
Groups of teams working together at the program level

17
00:00:49.070 --> 00:00:53.040
are formed into Agile Release Trains or ARTs.

18
00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:55.070
All the teams within an ART collaborate

19
00:00:55.070 --> 00:00:58.050
around a product increment or PI.

20
00:00:58.050 --> 00:01:01.040
In SAFe, the PIs are on a cadence

21
00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:05.000
or schedule that releases in unison.

22
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:09.010
Usually the PI is three months or a quarter in length.

23
00:01:09.010 --> 00:01:13.020
At the portfolio level, SAFe has created a detailed model

24
00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:16.040
around how organizations can select

25
00:01:16.040 --> 00:01:18.030
the right work to complete.

26
00:01:18.030 --> 00:01:20.050
It also helps sequence the order

27
00:01:20.050 --> 00:01:23.040
of the work flowing into an ART.

28
00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:25.010
Work is funneled to the ARTs

29
00:01:25.010 --> 00:01:27.000
from the portfolio management team

30
00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:30.080
that approves work based on organizational objectives.

31
00:01:30.080 --> 00:01:33.060
Then related work items are sequenced

32
00:01:33.060 --> 00:01:35.090
to create product increments.

33
00:01:35.090 --> 00:01:37.090
Fannie Mae chose the SAFe model

34
00:01:37.090 --> 00:01:40.020
because it focuses on continuous

35
00:01:40.020 --> 00:01:43.030
integration and early testing.

36
00:01:43.030 --> 00:01:47.090
Adopting Agile and SAFe allowed them to mitigate risk.

37
00:01:47.090 --> 00:01:51.000
Fannie Mae has seen a couple of results.

38
00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Reduced risk through their focus

39
00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:56.040
on automation and continuous integration.

40
00:01:56.040 --> 00:01:58.010
Dramatically improved quality

41
00:01:58.010 --> 00:02:02.070
as evidenced by significantly reduced defect rates.

42
