Let's look at the pros and cons of the SAFe model

43
00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:08.030
to help you get started with your decision.

44
00:02:08.030 --> 00:02:11.000
On the pro side this is the most

45
00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.040
popular scaling model out there.

46
00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:15.090
Since it's so prevalent it's easy

47
00:02:15.090 --> 00:02:18.000
for an organization to find the training

48
00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.090
and coaching they need to support their roll out.

49
00:02:21.090 --> 00:02:25.000
SAFe even provides a detailed roadmap

50
00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.010
telling you how to implement it.

51
00:02:27.010 --> 00:02:30.000
SAFe is well suited to large organizations

52
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:32.060
and emphasizes establishing teams

53
00:02:32.060 --> 00:02:35.080
that stay together for a long time.

54
00:02:35.080 --> 00:02:37.050
On the con side of SAFe.

55
00:02:37.050 --> 00:02:39.010
First, since you're being told

56
00:02:39.010 --> 00:02:41.020
what to do to roll it out

57
00:02:41.020 --> 00:02:44.000
you don't have to have deep organizational

58
00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.000
understanding of why you're doing it.

